            ("p", "It surprises a lot of owners, but a small local business can — and frequently does — outrank national chains in local search results. The reason is encouraging: Google's local algorithm rewards a set of signals that money alone can't buy, and several of them favor the genuinely local business over the distant corporate one. Here's why the little guy so often wins the map pack."),
